UNDATED (KTHV) – 247Sports.com , a partner with CBSSports.com , is reporting that former North Little Rock High School running back Altee Tenpenny died in a car accident Tuesday night. 
Tenpenny committed to Crimson Tide on 2012 but left the program in 2015 for University of Nevada – Las Vegas. He was later dismissed and ended up at Nicholls State in the same month.
